00:49:20.970 --> 00:49:24.270 align:middle line:84%
Even though it looks like fun,
you are deeply researched.

00:49:24.270 --> 00:49:26.511 align:middle line:84%
You have a lot that's going
on behind what we see.

00:49:26.511 --> 00:49:28.010 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: Kind
of and kind of not.

00:49:28.010 --> 00:49:29.520 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't trained as a chef.

00:49:29.520 --> 00:49:30.420 align:middle line:90%
I just like to cook.

00:49:30.420 --> 00:49:30.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's amazing.

00:49:30.840 --> 00:49:32.923 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: I said I'm
just do I'm doing this show

00:49:32.923 --> 00:49:34.590 align:middle line:90%
and sharing my recipes with you.

00:49:34.590 --> 00:49:36.037 align:middle line:90%
And it just took off.

00:49:36.037 --> 00:49:37.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, but
you pulled this out.

00:49:37.620 --> 00:49:39.645 align:middle line:90%
And you really did make it work.

00:49:39.645 --> 00:49:40.890 align:middle line:90%
Where do you live now?

00:49:40.890 --> 00:49:42.484 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned you
lived on a farm?

00:49:42.484 --> 00:49:44.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: Yeah, I just
moved from Sedona, Arizona,

00:49:44.650 --> 00:49:47.730 align:middle line:84%
which was my beloved place,
my beloved community and home.

00:49:47.730 --> 00:49:49.000 align:middle line:90%
And the time's up for it.

00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:52.510 align:middle line:84%
So I move back to
California to the home

00:49:52.510 --> 00:49:55.140 align:middle line:90%
my father built in the country.

00:49:55.140 --> 00:49:57.240 align:middle line:84%
So we live in the
Sierra Foothills.

00:49:57.240 --> 00:50:00.720 align:middle line:84%
And we have a lovely Satsuma
Mandarin orange orchard that

00:50:00.720 --> 00:50:02.760 align:middle line:90%
is a small commercial orchard.

00:50:02.760 --> 00:50:05.090 align:middle line:84%
And it's an area
that's no growth.

00:50:05.090 --> 00:50:06.870 align:middle line:84%
So the next city
over sells their land

00:50:06.870 --> 00:50:08.100 align:middle line:90%
to the highest bidder.

00:50:08.100 --> 00:50:11.640 align:middle line:84%
Nothing but shopping malls,
big box stores, and you

00:50:11.640 --> 00:50:14.220 align:middle line:84%
drive across the railroad
tracks into our town and nothing

00:50:14.220 --> 00:50:16.680 align:middle line:84%
but potholes and minimum
of five acre lots.

00:50:16.680 --> 00:50:18.470 align:middle line:90%
So it's very, very country.

00:50:18.470 --> 00:50:20.059 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's no
growth limit on it?

00:50:20.059 --> 00:50:21.600 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: Oh,
yeah, the people that

00:50:21.600 --> 00:50:23.947 align:middle line:84%
live there don't want any
intrusion in the two towns.

00:50:23.947 --> 00:50:25.530 align:middle line:84%
I live right on the
border of the two.

00:50:25.530 --> 00:50:28.620 align:middle line:84%
And the total population is
8,000 between both towns.

00:50:28.620 --> 00:50:32.100 align:middle line:84%
And they won't allow
growth to happen,

00:50:32.100 --> 00:50:33.300 align:middle line:90%
which I'm very thankful for.

00:50:33.300 --> 00:50:34.100 align:middle line:90%
No developments.

00:50:34.100 --> 00:50:35.640 align:middle line:90%
So it's just farms.

00:50:35.640 --> 00:50:39.180 align:middle line:84%
And so people are coming
in from LA and the Bay Area

00:50:39.180 --> 00:50:42.740 align:middle line:84%
and snapping up the land and
building their McMansions

00:50:42.740 --> 00:50:45.350 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of vineyards
have gone in recently.

00:50:45.350 --> 00:50:48.400 align:middle line:84%
It's considered the new
wine growing region.

00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:51.080 align:middle line:84%
The DuPonts bought the
property two doors down

00:50:51.080 --> 00:50:53.390 align:middle line:84%
and put a vineyard in
and a wine tasting room.

00:50:53.390 --> 00:50:56.000 align:middle line:84%
But they still have to comply
to the local standards.

00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:56.960 align:middle line:90%
It's privately owned.

00:50:56.960 --> 00:50:58.640 align:middle line:84%
And they're living
by the standards.

00:50:58.640 --> 00:51:02.547 align:middle line:84%
But it's kind of you're
feeling now the kind of--

00:51:02.547 --> 00:51:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Progression.

00:51:03.380 --> 00:51:04.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: --progression.

00:51:04.250 --> 00:51:05.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It happens.

00:51:05.050 --> 00:51:06.280 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: It happens, yeah.

00:51:06.280 --> 00:51:08.238 align:middle line:84%
You know, people just
want to enjoy the country

00:51:08.238 --> 00:51:09.720 align:middle line:90%
and get away from being crowded.

00:51:09.720 --> 00:51:10.520 align:middle line:90%
Including me.

00:51:10.520 --> 00:51:12.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're also
able to get out.

00:51:12.480 --> 00:51:14.630 align:middle line:84%
You are still very
busy and you work.

00:51:14.630 --> 00:51:16.760 align:middle line:84%
And then you can come back
to a place that is home.

00:51:16.760 --> 00:51:19.250 align:middle line:84%
And you have--
I've heard you talk

00:51:19.250 --> 00:51:23.240 align:middle line:84%
about beauty as being a very
important aspect of your life.

00:51:23.240 --> 00:51:25.230 align:middle line:84%
Can you share that
with us a little bit?

00:51:25.230 --> 00:51:27.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: It always has
been, since I remember,

00:51:27.440 --> 00:51:30.380 align:middle line:84%
since I was two or
three years old.

00:51:30.380 --> 00:51:33.080 align:middle line:84%
I just understood
something about

00:51:33.080 --> 00:51:37.790 align:middle line:84%
flowers and beautiful colors
and symmetry and so forth.

00:51:37.790 --> 00:51:40.280 align:middle line:84%
And then I started studying
it and just kind of looking

00:51:40.280 --> 00:51:41.510 align:middle line:90%
into it more as time went on.

00:51:41.510 --> 00:51:43.580 align:middle line:84%
And recently,
interviewed a man whom

00:51:43.580 --> 00:51:48.606 align:middle line:84%
I adore, Stephen Ross, on the
subject of beauty on my site.

00:51:48.606 --> 00:51:49.730 align:middle line:90%
And we went in it together.

00:51:49.730 --> 00:51:51.920 align:middle line:84%
And we've tracked each
other in our lives,

00:51:51.920 --> 00:51:54.380 align:middle line:84%
a lot of the work we've
done for the last 30 years,

00:51:54.380 --> 00:51:57.050 align:middle line:90%
and Stephen--

00:51:57.050 --> 00:51:58.700 align:middle line:84%
and the point of
the conversation

00:51:58.700 --> 00:52:03.680 align:middle line:84%
is that beauty adds refinement
to anything you apply it to.

00:52:03.680 --> 00:52:06.920 align:middle line:84%
And beauty can be something as
simple as a smile to a clerk

00:52:06.920 --> 00:52:08.330 align:middle line:90%
who's having a rough day--

00:52:08.330 --> 00:52:10.910 align:middle line:90%
that's an act of beauty--

00:52:10.910 --> 00:52:15.106 align:middle line:84%
to literally creating something,
creating something beautiful,

00:52:15.106 --> 00:52:16.730 align:middle line:84%
like what you do on
your show, creating

00:52:16.730 --> 00:52:19.070 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful environment,
and inviting people

00:52:19.070 --> 00:52:20.790 align:middle line:84%
in in a beautiful
way to talk with you.

00:52:20.790 --> 00:52:22.460 align:middle line:90%
That's an act of beauty.

00:52:22.460 --> 00:52:26.600 align:middle line:84%
You can paint your house
a lovely, soft turquoise

00:52:26.600 --> 00:52:28.190 align:middle line:90%
that soothes the eyes.

00:52:28.190 --> 00:52:33.410 align:middle line:84%
But every time you commit
yourself to an act of beauty,

00:52:33.410 --> 00:52:37.460 align:middle line:84%
you're raising the
frequency of your field.

00:52:37.460 --> 00:52:40.370 align:middle line:84%
It goes up, up, up, up,
every act of beauty.

00:52:40.370 --> 00:52:42.034 align:middle line:90%
And that starts with thoughts.

00:52:42.034 --> 00:52:43.450 align:middle line:84%
And we all have
negative thoughts.

00:52:43.450 --> 00:52:44.870 align:middle line:90%
We all get mad.

00:52:44.870 --> 00:52:47.120 align:middle line:84%
But, yet, if you can recover
yourself and return it

00:52:47.120 --> 00:52:48.350 align:middle line:90%
to something beautiful.

00:52:48.350 --> 00:52:50.450 align:middle line:84%
For me, a lot of times
it's just deciding I

00:52:50.450 --> 00:52:52.460 align:middle line:84%
want to bake something
for my friends.

00:52:52.460 --> 00:52:54.960 align:middle line:90%
Baking for me is like a therapy.

00:52:54.960 --> 00:52:56.420 align:middle line:90%
It's very, very soothing.

00:52:56.420 --> 00:52:58.760 align:middle line:84%
And I love sharing
it with other people.

00:52:58.760 --> 00:53:00.830 align:middle line:84%
So I just get in the
kitchen and pull out

00:53:00.830 --> 00:53:04.190 align:middle line:84%
my apron and my stuff,
my gluten free stuff.

00:53:04.190 --> 00:53:05.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Your gluten free stuff.

00:53:05.730 --> 00:53:07.130 align:middle line:84%
I love what you
say about beauty.

00:53:07.130 --> 00:53:08.410 align:middle line:90%
I agree.

00:53:08.410 --> 00:53:10.760 align:middle line:84%
Beauty makes things
calm and quiet for me.

00:53:10.760 --> 00:53:11.560 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Yes.

00:53:11.560 --> 00:53:12.476 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And it's not--

00:53:12.476 --> 00:53:14.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm not talking about
facial beauty and clothes.

00:53:14.720 --> 00:53:18.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking about just
calm, serene, beauty.

00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:20.630 align:middle line:84%
The beauty of a flower
and how it blooms.

00:53:20.630 --> 00:53:23.937 align:middle line:84%
And a strawberry and
the lines of the seeds.

00:53:23.937 --> 00:53:26.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: This was very
important in ancient cultures,

00:53:26.270 --> 00:53:29.710 align:middle line:84%
ancient Persian,
Chinese, Japanese.

00:53:29.710 --> 00:53:34.661 align:middle line:84%
Beauty was the ultimate to
aspire to on all levels.

00:53:34.661 --> 00:53:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Even though there were other
factors of those societies that

00:53:37.160 --> 00:53:40.685 align:middle line:84%
could be quite
cruel in the day, it

00:53:40.685 --> 00:53:43.490 align:middle line:84%
was still an aspiration to
live in a more beautiful way.

00:53:43.490 --> 00:53:44.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:53:44.290 --> 00:53:45.498 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: It's not anymore.

00:53:45.498 --> 00:53:46.610 align:middle line:90%
That's gone.

00:53:46.610 --> 00:53:49.130 align:middle line:84%
The thing that's so
wonderful about beauty to me

00:53:49.130 --> 00:53:51.050 align:middle line:84%
is that we were
talking about time

00:53:51.050 --> 00:53:52.580 align:middle line:84%
and how we get
frustrated because we

00:53:52.580 --> 00:53:54.470 align:middle line:84%
can't manifest the
big stuff that takes

00:53:54.470 --> 00:53:56.270 align:middle line:90%
a buy in from other people.

00:53:56.270 --> 00:53:59.150 align:middle line:84%
With little acts of beauty
like baking something, doing

00:53:59.150 --> 00:54:02.810 align:middle line:84%
a little painting, just going
over and helping someone,

00:54:02.810 --> 00:54:04.670 align:middle line:84%
those things you
can do in real time

00:54:04.670 --> 00:54:07.100 align:middle line:84%
and have real, on Earth
time satisfaction,

00:54:07.100 --> 00:54:09.560 align:middle line:90%
like now, instant gratification.

00:54:09.560 --> 00:54:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Those acts of beauty
make it possible to be

00:54:13.220 --> 00:54:15.880 align:middle line:84%
patient through the rest
of the really big stuff

00:54:15.880 --> 00:54:17.880 align:middle line:84%
while raising your
frequencies at the same time.

00:54:17.880 --> 00:54:21.230 align:middle line:84%
So I'm really big on just engage
in any little act of beauty

00:54:21.230 --> 00:54:23.210 align:middle line:84%
you can any time
it presents itself,

00:54:23.210 --> 00:54:25.840 align:middle line:84%
because that is instant
gratification in this realm.

00:54:25.840 --> 00:54:27.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so important.

00:54:27.050 --> 00:54:29.300 align:middle line:84%
That is very necessary
with all the things

00:54:29.300 --> 00:54:30.900 align:middle line:90%
we have going on in our world.

00:54:30.900 --> 00:54:32.790 align:middle line:84%
I like to ask my guests,
what is your biggest

00:54:32.790 --> 00:54:35.925 align:middle line:90%
why for why you do what you do?

00:54:35.925 --> 00:54:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: Pretty
much because of what

00:54:37.550 --> 00:54:40.560 align:middle line:84%
we've been talking about
just a little bit ago.

00:54:40.560 --> 00:54:42.800 align:middle line:84%
I see that people
are struggling.

00:54:42.800 --> 00:54:44.450 align:middle line:84%
And the only reason
they're struggling

00:54:44.450 --> 00:54:46.740 align:middle line:84%
is because they're not
listening to themselves.

00:54:46.740 --> 00:54:49.670 align:middle line:84%
So if you can help
somebody learn to dial back

00:54:49.670 --> 00:54:53.390 align:middle line:84%
into themselves and their
incredible true nature,

00:54:53.390 --> 00:54:55.460 align:middle line:84%
then you don't have
these questions.

00:54:55.460 --> 00:54:57.386 align:middle line:84%
And this kind of
despair that we're

00:54:57.386 --> 00:54:59.510 align:middle line:84%
seeing on the planet, the
distraction we're seeing,

00:54:59.510 --> 00:55:00.560 align:middle line:90%
there's no need for it.

00:55:00.560 --> 00:55:01.790 align:middle line:90%
You're dialed in.

00:55:01.790 --> 00:55:03.770 align:middle line:10%
So what I do is
simply to give people

00:55:03.770 --> 00:55:06.170 align:middle line:10%
a lot of different
perspectives-- all of them,

00:55:06.170 --> 00:55:07.880 align:middle line:10%
all of the paths lead to Rome.

00:55:07.880 --> 00:55:10.167 align:middle line:84%
Start dialing back
into your true self.

00:55:10.167 --> 00:55:11.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love that.

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:14.510 align:middle line:84%
I love that you shared so
many things with us about how

00:55:14.510 --> 00:55:15.916 align:middle line:90%
to live an inspired life.

00:55:15.916 --> 00:55:17.540 align:middle line:84%
That really is truly
what you're doing.

00:55:17.540 --> 00:55:19.400 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: That's the
way I do it, anyway.

